{"name": "spaceboi", "metadata": {"name": "spaceboi", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/ericpar234/spaceboi", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["skyfield", "requests", "pytz", "PyQt5", "matplotlib", "numpy", "Basemap", "darkdetect"], "summary": "A radio satellite event tracker.", "upload_time": 1732984484}, "documentation": ["![spaceboi](cover.png)\n\n\n# Spaceboi\n\nSpaceboi gives you the sat events. Period.\n\nA simple satellite pass predictor using TLE data from celestrak.org. It can be\nrun in a GUI mode or CLI mode. The GUI mode uses Qt to display the passes in a\ntable, and graph the current events. The CLI mode prints the passes to the\nconsole. The passes can also be plotted using the plot mode.\n\n# Install\n\nClone the repo and install the requirements\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\nor \n\nInstall from pypi\n```\npip install spaceboi\n```\n\n\n# Configuration\n\nThe config file by default is stored in ~/.config/spaceboi/config.json. The GUI\nsettings will automatically be saved to this file. The config file can also be\nmanually specified using the --config option.\n\nExample config.json\n```json\n{\n    \"urls\": [\n        \"https://celestrak.org/NORAD/elements/gp.php?GROUP=weather&FORMAT=json\",\n        \"https://celestrak.org/NORAD/elements/gp.php?GROUP=amateur&FORMAT=json\",\n    ],\n    \"lat\": 40.7128,\n    \"lon\": -74.006,\n    \"timezone\": \"America/New_York\",\n    \"filter_enabled\": true,\n    \"satellites\": [\n        \"NOAA 15\",\n        \"NOAA 18\",\n        \"NOAA 19\",\n        \"METEOR-M2 2\",\n        \"METEOR-M2 3\",\n        \"ISS (ZARYA)\",\n        \"GOES 18\"\n    ],\n    \"min_alt\": 10,\n    \"hours\": 24,\n    \"mode\": \"gui\",\n    \"config\": \"config.json\"\n}\n```\n\n- urls: list of urls to fetch TLE data from. For now JSON format is supported\n- lat: latitude of observer\n- lon: longitude of observer\n- timezone: timezone of observer\n- filter_enabled: filter satellites by name\n- satellites: list of satellites for the filter\n- min_alt: minimum altitude to display\n- hours: number of hours ahead to predict\n- mode: the default mode to run the program in\n- config: the path to the config file\n\n# Usage\n\n```bash\n# A gui to view passes\npython spaceboi.py --mode gui\n\n# Print the passes\npython spaceboi.py --mode cli\n\n# or\n\n# Plot the passes\npython spaceboi.py --mode plot\n```\n\nAll config options can be used as command line arguments. For example:\n\n```bash\npython spaceboi.py gui \\\n--lat 40.7128 --lon -74.006 --timezone \"America/New_York\" \\\n--filter_enabled true \\\n--satellites \"NOAA 15\" \"NOAA 18\" \"NOAA 19\" \"METEOR-M2 2\" \"METEOR-M2 3\" \"ISS (ZARYA)\" \"GOES 18\" \\\n--min_alt 10 --hours 24 --config \"config.json\"\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "spaceboi", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "spaceboi.calcPasses", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "satellite", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "startTime", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "hours", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "topo", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "minAltitude", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.formatPass", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "satPass", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "local_tz", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.plot_event", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "satellite", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "event", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ts", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "topo", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Plots a single satellite pass event on a polar plot.\nParameters:\n    event (dict): A dictionary containing event details.\n    ax (PolarAxesSubplot, optional): Existing polar plot axis. If None, a new one will be created."]}, {"name": "spaceboi.plot_events", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "satellites", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "events", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ts", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "topo", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Plots multiple satellite pass events on a single polar plot.\nParameters:\n    events (list): List of dictionaries containing event details."]}, {"name": "spaceboi.initialize_map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ax", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.plot_map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "satellites", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ts", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ax", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "my_map", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "selected", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.fetchData", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.fetchAllData", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ts", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mode", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "spaceboi.dark_stylesheet", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "spaceboi.DEFAULT_CONFIG", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "spaceboi.WorkerSignals", "bases": ["QObject"], "methods": []